01/05/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbia wants a "real compromise solution" for Kosovo, President Boris Tadic said on Thursday (April 30th), expressing confidence that Kosovo officials will return to the bargaining table. 
In an interview with Vecernje Novosti, he said Kosovo cannot become an UN member without Serbia's agreement. 
"This fact will be will make Kosovo officials return to the negotiating process sooner or later," he said.
At the same time, Tadic ruled out any Serbian action against the self-declared state. 
"One thing is sure. 
Democratic Serbia will never lead a war; it will not threaten its citizens or the region. 
We want the best possible relations with the Albanians despite the marks of the past," he said. 
(AFP, Vecernje Novosti - 30/04/09)
